sentences: Ayame Goriki (剛力 彩芽, Gōriki Ayame, born 27 August 1992) is a Japanese actress, singer and model from Hodogaya-ku, Yokohama, Kanagawa Prefecture.
She was represented by the talent agency Oscar Promotion until 2020.
Goriki also participated in the 8th Japan Beautiful Girl Contest in 2002, but did not progress past the second round.
In January 2011, she appeared on the Fuji TV monthly drama Taisetsu na Koto wa Subete Kimi ga Oshiete Kureta.
However, her official debut work is ChocoMimi (TV Tokyo), premiering in 2007.
In November 2011, Nikkei Trendy selected her as "Face of the Year".

In 2016, she performed live for the first time in the Meiji-za November performance of Sisters of the Gion.
In 2012, she voiced Elizabeth Shaw in the movie Prometheus.
In 2014, she also voiced Mystique in X-Men: Days of Future Past.

In July of the same year, she starred in a TV drama "Cosmic Star" for TV Tokyo's IS.
In November 2011, Nikkei Trendy selected her as "Face of the Year".
In 2016, she performed live for the first time in the Meiji-za November performance of Sisters of the Gion.
